Title : List of Haitian flags
Text : This is a list of flags used in '''[[Haiti]]'''. For more information about the national flag, visit the article [[Flag of Haiti]].

== National flag ==

{| border="2" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse;"
|-  bgcolor="#efefef"
! width="110"|Flag!!width="100"|Date!!width="250"|Use!!width="250"|Description
|-
|[[File:Pavillon LouisXIV.svg|100px|border]]
|'''1625-1790'''
|Flag of [[Saint-Domingue]]
|The crown represents the [[Kingdom of France]].
|-
|[[File:Flag of Haiti (1791-1789).svg|border|100px]]
|'''1791-1798'''
|Flag of [[Saint-Domingue]]
|Marquis de Caradeu, with supposed powers from the French Assembly, established his power in the island. His flag was "used for all the nation."
|-
|[[File:Flag of France.svg|100px|border]]
|'''1798-1803'''
|Flag of [[Saint-Domingue]]
|The [[Tricolour (flag)|tricolour]] flag of the [[French First Republic]] was adopted in 1798 by [[Toussaint Louverture]] after the [[French Revolution]].<ref name="Haiti.org">{{cite web|url=http://haiti.org/index.php/component/content/article/26-the-embassy/content/122-flag-and-coat-of-arms|title=Flag and Coat of Arms|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426215048/http://haiti.org/index.php/component/content/article/26-the-embassy/content/122-flag-and-coat-of-arms|archivedate=26 April 2014|deadurl=yes|accessdate=25 April 2014|df=}}</ref>
|-
|[[File:Flag of Haiti (1803-1804).svg|100px|border]]
|'''1803'''
|Revolutionary flag of [[Saint-Domingue]]
|Jean-Jacques Dessalines, chief of the black rebels, and Alexandre Pétion, leader of the mulattoes, decide in 1803 to stop fighting alongside the French. On May 18, 1803, Dessalines removes the white band from the French flag and has his relative, [[Catherine Flon]], sew together the blue and red bands together to form the first Haitian flag symbolizing the alliance between the blacks and mulattoes. Dessalines  orders that the words ''Liberté ou la mort'' (Freedom or death), be inscribed on the flag.<ref name="Haiti.org" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ozoutback.com.au/Haiti/flags/index.html|title=A Flag history of Haiti|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>
|-
|[[File:Flag of Haiti (civil).svg|100px|border]]
|'''1804 '''
|
|The first flag of the Republic. The generals of the revolution decided to change the flag so that the bands are horizontal.<ref name="Haiti.org" />
|-
|[[File:Flag of Haiti 1964 (civil).svg|100px|border]]
|'''1804-1806 '''
|Flag of the [[First Empire of Haiti]].
|Flag of the First Empire, used by [[Jean-Jacques Dessalines]] who proclaimed himself Emperor under the name of Jacques I. He adopted a new flag on 20 May 1805: the blue band was changed to black to symbolize ''death'' (black) and ''freedom'' (red).<ref name="Haiti.org" /><ref name="crwflags">{{cite web|url=http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/ht-hist.html|title=Haiti - Historical Flags|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>
|-
| [[File:Flag of Haiti 1806.svg|100px]] || '''1806-1811 || Flag of the [[State of Haiti]] || Flag of the Northern State, used by President [[Henri Christophe]], who adopted the bicolors from the flag of the [[Haitian Revolution]].<ref name="Haiti.org" /><ref name="crwflags" />
|-
| [[File:Flag of Haiti (1811–1814).png|100px]] || '''1811–1814 || Flag of the [[Kingdom of Haiti]] || 
|-
| [[File:Flag of Kingdom of Haiti.svg|100px]] || '''1814–1820 || Flag of the [[Kingdom of Haiti]] || Flag of the Northern Kingdom, used by [[Henri Christophe]], who proclaimed himself King, under the name of [[Henri Christophe|Henri I]], who maintained the imperial flag of Dessalines inverting colors of red in the hoist and black in the fly with, in the center, adding a shield with a phoenix under five five-pointed stars, all in gold on a blue background; the shield bore a crown and the Latin inscription, ''Ex Cinerebus Nascitur''.<ref name="Haiti.org" /><ref name="crwflags" />
|-
| [[File:Flag of Haiti (1849-1859).png|100px|border]] || '''1849–1859|| Flag of the [[Second Empire of Haiti]] || An attempt to restore the black and red flag which was made in 1844 failed. In 1847, [[Faustin Soulouque]] was elected president and in 1849 he proclaimed himself Emperor under the name of Faustin I, who kept the blue and red band, but changed the coat of arms with his own in representation of his monarch rule.<ref name="Haiti.org" /><ref name="crwflags" />
|-
| [[File:Flag of Haiti (1964-1986).svg|100px|border]] || '''1964–1986 || Flag of Haiti used by the [[François Duvalier|Duvaliers]] || The new constitution under Duvalier returns to the black and red flag first used by Dessalines, although the coat of arms remains but with color modifications instead of the blue, with black.<ref name="Haiti.org" />
|-
|[[File:Flag of Haiti (1859–1964).svg|100px|border]]
|'''1820-1849,<br>1859-1964'''
|Flag of the [[Unification of Hispaniola]] and Flag of the [[Republic of Haiti (1859–1957)|First Haitian Republic]] (1859–1964).
|The bicolour flag of 1804, reverted to use by [[Alexandre Pétion]] to represent the Republic, while also adopting the [[Coat of arms of Haiti|coat of arms]] at the center with the inscription, ''L'union fait la force'' (unity makes strength).<ref name="Haiti.org" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nationsflags.blogspot.com/2010/02/republic-of-haiti.html|title=The Republic of Haiti|accessdate=4 June 2014}}</ref>
|-
|[[File:Flag of Haiti.svg|100px|border]]
|'''1986-Present'''
|'''[[Flag of Haiti]] '''
|''See previous flag.''
|-
|}

